org.apache.beam.sdk.io.hdfs

Class HDFSFileSink<T,K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.sdk.io.Sink<T>
      • org.apache.beam.sdk.io.hdfs.HDFSFileSink<T,K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements of the input PCollection.
    K - the type of keys to be written to the sink via FileOutputFormat.
    V - the type of values to be written to the sink via FileOutputFormat.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, HasDisplayData

    public abstract class HDFSFileSink<T,K,V>
extends Sink<T>
    A Sink for writing records to a Hadoop filesystem using a Hadoop file-based output format.

    To write a PCollection of elements of type T to Hadoop filesystem use to(java.lang.String, java.lang.Class<W>, java.lang.Class<K>, java.lang.Class<V>, org.apache.beam.sdk.transforms.SerializableFunction<T, org.apache.beam.sdk.values.KV<K, V>>), specify the path (this can be any Hadoop supported filesystem: HDFS, S3, GCS etc), the Hadoop FileOutputFormat, the key class K and the value class V and finally the SerializableFunction to map from T to KV of K and V.

    HDFSFileSink can be used by Write to create write transform. See example below.

    HDFSFileSink comes with helper methods to write text and Apache Avro. For example: 

     
 HDFSFileSink<CustomSpecificAvroClass, AvroKey<CustomSpecificAvroClass>, NullWritable> sink =
   HDFSFileSink.toAvro(path, AvroCoder.of(CustomSpecificAvroClass.class));
 avroRecordsPCollection.apply(Write.to(sink));
